Description: Use pkg-config to detect libsystemd
 In Debian Trixie libsystemd-dev only ships libsystemd.so via the
 pkg-config file; a bare -lsystemd link check fails because the
 unversioned .so symlink is not guaranteed to exist. Switch the
 systemd auto-option to use pkg-config so the resulting uselib is
 named SYSTEMD, matching what jackd uses.
Author: pistomp <pistomp@example.com>
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-06-22

--- a/wscript
+++ b/wscript
@@ -195,7 +195,10 @@ def options(opt):
             'systemd',
             help='Use systemd notify')
     sd.check(header_name='systemd/sd-daemon.h')
-    sd.check(lib='systemd')
+    sd.check_cfg(
+            package='libsystemd',
+            args='--cflags --libs',
+            uselib_store='SYSTEMD')
     db = opt.add_auto_option(
             'db',
             help='Use Berkeley DB (metadata)')
